relevant_findings.HEENT: Sclera anicteric, dry mucous membranes, oropharynx clear
relevant_findings.neck: Supple, JVP not elevated, no lymphadenopathy
relevant_findings.lungs: Clear to auscultation anteriorly, no wheezes, rales, or rhonchi
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, normal S1/S2, soft grade II/VI systolic ejection murmur over left upper sternal border
relevant_findings.abdomen: Soft, mild diffuse tenderness to palpation, bowel sounds present, no guarding
relevant_findings.extremities: Warm, well perfused, 2+ pulses, no clubbing, cyanosis, or edema
